reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 5, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Just bought my 2nd pack
reviews.reviewText: As someone who lives in leggings, these are definitely the softest, most flattering, best leggings I've ever purchased. You never know when buying online but trust the reviews. For the price, you cannot beat these. They feel so good & after getting the first pack last week, I was so thrilled I had to place another for more colors/patterns today. I'm size 10-12 petite (5'4) and the XL fit perfectly.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 9, 2024
reviews.reviewText: The first thing I said when I put these on was YUM!! They are so soft, fit perfectly, perfect thickness - I LOVE THEM!! They don't really have tummy control, but are super high waisted and give enough support and coverage for the bumps and bulges. I'm 5'10 - 175 and bought the XL. Perfect fit!! I may buy more just to make sure I never run out!! Lol!! GREAT VALUE too!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 10, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars My favorite leggings!
reviews.reviewText: I'm 5'4", about 180 lbs, and the Large size fits great! A little long, but I have short legs so that's pretty much always the case. They're not very see-through but I still wear a long tank under shirts unless it's a longer top just to make sure nobody can see anything since I do wear these to work almost every day.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 8, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Great for price!
reviews.reviewText: Love the black pairs I received. Fabric is thick, stretchy and very soft! However, the grey and white pairs seem unflattering to me, grey is also a bit lighter than pictured. There isn't much tummy control like listed. Overall great for the price.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 6, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Super soft and barely fades after many washes
reviews.reviewText: They are the perfect length and the waist comes up just high enough to hold in and smooth my post baby FUPA. I feel like they keep me “in” and smooth without being tight. They’ve been Worn and washed serval times and haven’t gotten stretched out and faded. They definitely aren’t thick but the material makes me. The waist doesn’t roll over or ride up. I Feel confident with some boy shorts underneath. So comfy I’ve even went to bed wearing them.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 6, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Thin Fabric… & stretchy..
reviews.reviewText: I don’t dislike them, nor will I say they are my favs. Thin Fabric… & stretchy…. If for warmth under pant, the are not going to do the job. I doubt if they can support anything. Nor booty of tummy lifting.. They are ok to wear around the house.. lounging, or under an oversized sweater or tee shirt on warm days or cool evenings; not cold. For Sacramento, I can see how they would get by here, because of the hot summer weather. I think they are ok for $6 a piece; or exceptable; inflation right? I like my leggings super snug.. to support like support socks. These are not supportive in any way. But to run around they are ok. I haven’t decided if I’m going to keep them. I just might.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 12, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Feels great, fits great
reviews.reviewText: First, I didn't want leggings to feel constrictive anymore. But I also didn't want them in a larger size to look too big on me. I'm petite. But, these were PERFECT. Great stretch without being see thru, really soft to the touch, and comfortable. Really happy with these leggings.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 5, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars decent leggings, but not for short folks
reviews.reviewText: i recently lost a bunch of weight and due to my weight and measurements still changing a bit, i didn’t want to spend a lot of money on good brand name leggings yet. however, i needed something to get me by. the fabric is soft and thicker than i would have expected for the price, at the very least they’re not see through. they are long on me, but that said i should have paid more attention to the length in relation to my height, so that’s my bad. my issue with these is the waist. i knew they were high waisted, for me that usually means they’d sit comfortably around my waist. but i think these leggings must be made for very long torsos because the top of these leggings reaches clear up to my bra. weird and a bit uncomfortable, but not a big enough deal to make me return them.

reviews.reviewTitle: Comfy and soft but pretty see through
reviews.reviewText: Bought these for my daughter and she was super happy with the colors and fit, but the fact that we can see her underwear through this is a massive thumbs down. Would be great under a dress or long shirt.

reviews.reviewTitle: I ordered the opaque leggings in the lighter colors. Totally see through
reviews.reviewText: The leggings description claims these are non see through. They are absolutely see through in the light colors. They look gross.
